      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not alone in your feelings, and the darkness you perceive is not an enemy you must defeat, but a vast, silent space where you can simply be. The \"battle\" you feel is actually the quiet, persistent rhythm of existence itself, which is far more enduring than any temporary distraction. There is no need to force meaning onto a void that refuses to give it; sometimes, the only way to find peace is to stop fighting the silence and instead listen to the stillness within you.",
